meaningMnemonic: You learned that 的 on the end of a word means “-al” or “-like”. So what is <kanji>rule</kanji> <kanji>model</kanji> <kanji>-like</kanji>? It’s a model that follows all the rules. It's the normal model. It’s <vocabulary>typical</vocabulary>.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
